org.openlca.io.maps

Class MapFactor<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openlca.io.maps.MapFactor<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the entity type

    public class MapFactor<T>
extends Object
    Describes a conversion factor when mapping to a given entity type. For example if there is a flow from a format A that is mapped to a format B a MapFactor could describe the factor for conversion of amounts for the flow in format A to the flow amounts in B.

        public double apply(double value)
        Applies this factor to the given value. In the entity mappings conversion factors should be always applied by multiplication which is what this method does.
